The common Objections against this easie admiss
                     •
                  on of all his Majesties Subjects into Companies of Merchants, are;

The means to prevent this Evil, by additional Penal Laws, and alterations of some of those now in being, were long under debate, by his Majesties command in the Cou
                        •
                     cil of Trade, who according to their duty, took great pains therein; and since, I have been informed the same things were under consideration in Parliament, so that I doubt not, but in due time we shall see some more effectual Laws enacted to this purpose, as well in relation to Ireland, (from whence the greatest of this mischief proceeds) as in England, then ever yet have been; yet I do utterly despair of ever seeing this Disease perfectly cured till the Causes thereof be removed, which I take to be;
